snippet: Two Palestinians were killed and several others were wounded as residents said that up to 1,000 troops entered the camp between Jerusalem and Ramallah.
abstract: Two Palestinian men are killed by Israeli forces during raid on West Bank refugee camp; Israeli officials claim soldiers, who had entered camp to demolish family home of suspect in murder of Israeli civilian, acted in self-defense after coming under fire.

byline.original: By RAMI NAZZAL and ISABEL KERSHNER
byline.contributor: Rami Nazzal reported from the Qalandiya refugee camp, and Isabel Kershner from Jerusalem.

lead_paragraph: Two Palestinians were killed and several others were wounded as residents said that up to 1,000 troops entered the camp between Jerusalem and Ramallah.

headline.main: Israeli Soldiers Raid West Bank Refugee Camp, Prompting Deadly Clashes
headline.print_headline: Deadly Clashes Erupt as Israeli Soldiers Raid Refugee Camp in West Bank
